 - Added depth-2 primary render-path end-to-end test coverage (frac-0102b): `tests/test_render_pass.py` now includes `RenderPassEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/pass_.py` public surface through one register → enable → quantity → gate → apply lifecycle: a three-rule stack registered out of canonical order (`R3`, `R1`, `R2`) with `R1` quantity-disabled, `R2` carrying `quantities={"R2": 0.5}`, and `R3` role-gated by `frozenset({"melody", "bass"})` canonicalizes to `("R1", "R2", "R3")` with `effective_k` returning `0.0`/`0.5`/`1.0`; the first `apply(...)` returns a `PerformedPart` whose `applied_rules` skip the disabled `R1`, whose `quantities` record all three effective `k` values, and whose score-tree trace carries structurally correct `rule_id`/`k`/`roles` entries for `R2` (no role gate) and `R3` (forwarded role-gate frozenset); the second `apply(...)` with `quantity_overrides={"R1": 0.75}` re-enables `R1` so `applied_rules == ("R1", "R2", "R3")` in canonical order with the override `k=0.75` reflected in both `quantities` and the trace; and a combined diagnostic of rule order, effective-k map, and both performed-part snapshots (with `frozenset` role gates explicitly converted to sorted lists) round-trips through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_render_pass_depth.py` pins the render-pass test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the module already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4619 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
 
 - Documented render-ablation depth baseline coverage (frac-0102a): `sdp/notes/frac-0102a-render-ablation-depth.md` locates `tests/test_render_ablation.py`, identifies the pre-depth-2 helper-level coverage for `ablate(...)`, `build_ablation_cases(...)`, `run_ablation_suite(...)`, and `summarize_ablation_suite(...)`, calls out outputs that were only smoke-checked, and lists concrete follow-up gaps. No render-ablation runtime behavior, locked assertions, dependencies, migrations, or startup identity wiring were changed.
